<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-24T19:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-24T19:36:00-05:00" n="609" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/338: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-24T18:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            24, 1920—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January
                                    26—12:09 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>19. Five of the most prominent men Unionist party including Doctor
                                Bianchi leader arrested this afternoon. Situation tense.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>